BROTH 
=============================================

Using the broth generator for my chicken soup this is what I got (it actually looks great): 
    cooking method:  pressure-cooker (I'd be willing to try a crock-pot here though)
    broth type:  regular broth
    cultural variation (or inspiration / techniques to use, perhaps):  Holy Trinity
    extra aromatic:  Fennel 
    extra herb:  Marjoram (dried)
        add toward the end of the soup making process, in the last 10-15 minutes of simmering. 
        Start with adding about 1/2 tsp dried per quart of soup, then adjust if needed 
        If it was fresh you'd start by adding 1 tsp per quart,
            and you'd add it it in the last 5 minutes (or even right before serving) to preserve the freshness
    extra herb:  Peppercorns
        Added during the broth making stage, at the beginning. 
        Strain them out with the rest of the solids when the broth is done. 
    extra umami:  Roasted Bones
    extra acid:  Lemon Juice/Zest
        Add this right before serving, at the very end. 
            It's acidic and volatile, if you add it too early it can lose flavor and become metallic tasting / overly sour
        Usually you add about 1-2 tsp per quart of soup. 
            You can also provide lemon wedges so people can adjust it themselves.
        Apparently this enhances herbs like Marjoram or Parsley, which is perfect. 
    parts to use:  Whole Chicken

    AIs recommendations for every 4 cups (1 quart) of water: 
        1 cup yellow onion (chopped) 
        1/2 cup celery (chopped) 
        1/2 cup carrot (chopped) 
        1/2 cup fennel (chopped) 

    



=============================================
EXPERIMENTAL INGREDIENTS
=============================================

My Experimental Ratios
This has more noodles & dill, and less onion / celery. 
It is a bit heavy on the garlic as well. 

1 whole chicken, about 4 lbs
7 & 1/3 cups chicken broth (maybe drink or remove 2/3rds of a cup after you make it for 8 cups)
3 carrots
2 & 1/3 stalks celery 
6/10ths yellow onion 
5 cloves garlic 
4 cups dry, medium egg noodles 
3 tbsp olive oil (for sauteing vegetables) 
3 sprigs fresh thyme 
5 tbsp dill 
1 bay leaf
salt & pepper to taste 

AIs Balanced Suggestion: 
chicken, 2-2.5 lbs (thighs, breasts, or whole chicken)
8 cups chicken broth 
2-3 medium carrots
2-3 stalks celery 
1 medium yellow onion 
2-4 cloves garlic 
3 cups dry, medium egg noodles 
1-2 tbsp olive oil (for sauteing vegetables) 
3-4 sprigs fresh thyme 
1-2 bay leaves
2-3 tbsp dill 
salt & pepper to taste 
1-2 tbsp lemon juice (optional) 

